  "prompt": "What universities does Inteliquent recruit new grads from? What majors are they looking for?",
  "response": "Inteliquent, now known as Bandwidth Inc. after being acquired in November 2021, recruits new graduates from various universities across the United States. While specific universities may vary from year to year, some of the universities that Inteliquent has recruited from in the past include:\n\n1. University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign\n2. University of Chicago\n3. Northwestern University\n4. Purdue University\n5. Illinois Institute of Technology\n6. DePaul University\n7. University of Michigan\n8. Georgia Institute of Technology\n\nAs for the majors they look for, Inteliquent typically recruits graduates with degrees in the following fields:\n\n1. Computer Science\n2. Computer Engineering\n3. Electrical Engineering\n4. Information Technology\n5. Telecommunications\n6. Business Administration (with a focus on technology or sales)\n7. Marketing (with a focus on technology or sales)\n\nPlease note that the information provided is based on past recruitment trends and may not reflect the current hiring practices of Bandwidth Inc. For the most accurate and up-to-date information, it is recommended to visit their official careers page or contact their human resources department directly.",
